{"headline": "\u2018Still Crazy After All These Years,\u2019 Two Ways", "body": "\n \n         \n\nMembers of the Atlanta-based pop band  \n are probably crazy after all the takes it took to nail the cover of Paul Simon\u2019s \u201cStill Crazy After All These Years.\u201d They finished it just last week, so we\u2019re among the first to see it. It\u2019s part of their monthly cover series, a gift to their fans. The band members, Scott Schwartz, Matt Lipkins and Adam Hoffman, met at Emory University. Their music offers a one-two punch of gorgeous harmonies and instrumentals. A heads up \u2013 they\u2019re working on a new album to be released in 2014. They successfully funded their first album via  \n, offering incentives to their fans like exclusive online concerts and personalized videos of song requests dedicated to individual fans.         \nThe Paul Simon Special (1977) - part 5/8 - Still Crazy After All These Years \nThe Shadowboxers | Still Crazy After All These Years \n\n \n         \n\nA video of Paul Simon discussing the  \n \u201cStill Crazy\u201d with Dick Cavett         \n\n \n from Emory Magazine         \n\nVideos of cover songs the band sang at the request of donors:         \n\n \n (John Mayer)         \n\n \n (Paul McCartney)         \n\n \n (Paul Simon)        ", "url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/08/booming/still-crazy-after-all-these-years-two-ways.html", "date": "2013-10-08", "description": "Paul Simon\u2019s hit gets new, tight harmonies from an Atlanta pop band, the Shadowboxers."}